cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the application of deep learning methods, specifically convolutional networks, for the classification of medical images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which deals with image processing and analysis. The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation and the training of reliable and accurate classifiers, which are topics that fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of medical images suggests a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia) and the use of deep learning methods suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
